The Mission Marketing Group plc Key Developments

The Mission Marketing Group plc, Annual General Meeting, Jun 19, 2017
May 14 17
The Mission Marketing Group plc, Annual General Meeting, Jun 19, 2017.


The Mission Marketing Group plc Announces Consolidated Earnings Results for the Year Ended December 31, 2016
Mar 23 17
The Mission Marketing Group plc announced consolidated earnings results for the year ended December 31, 2016. For the full year, the company reported Turnover was £144,096,000 against turnover of £132,246,000 a year ago. Operating income was £65,898,000 against operating income of £61,037,000 a year ago. Headline operating profit was £7,557,000 against headline operating profit of £6,930,000 a year ago. Operating profit was £6,400,000 against operating profit of £5,606,000 a year ago. Profit before taxation was £5,880,000 against profit before taxation of £5,137,000 a year ago. Profit for the year attributable to equity holders was the parent of 4,434 pence against profit for the year attributable to equity holders of the parent of 4,011 pence a year ago. Diluted earnings per share were 5.19 pence against diluted earnings per share of 4.68 pence a year ago. Headline diluted earnings per share of 6.41 against headline diluted earnings per share of 5.91 a year ago. Net cash inflow from operating activities was £6,201,000 against net cash inflow from operating activities of £2,408,000 a year ago. Purchase of property, plant and equipment was £914,000 against purchase of property, plant and equipment of £1,295,000 a year ago.


The Mission Marketing Group plc Recommends Final Dividend, Payable on July 24, 2017
Mar 23 17
The board of The Mission Marketing Group plc recommended a final dividend of 1.0 pence per share, bringing the total for the year to 1.5 pence per share, representing an increase of 25% over 2015. The final dividend will be payable on July 24, 2017 to shareholders on the register at July 14, 2017. The corresponding ex-dividend date is July 13, 2017.


